#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:384
msgid ""
"Settlers are one of the key units in the game, as they are your main means "
"of founding new cities, and can also improve terrain. See the help on "
"Terrain and Terrain Alterations."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:388
msgid ""
"Upkeep for Settlers is in food as well as production, and a Settler can die "
"if its supporting city runs out of food. Settlers require twice as much food "
"per turn under Republic, Democracy, Communism, or Fundamentalism."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:396 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:597
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:531 data/experimental/units.ruleset:548
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:532 data/royale/units.ruleset:694
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:601
msgid "Engineers"
msgstr "Inĝenieroj"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:422
msgid ""
"Engineers are similar to Settlers, but they work twice as fast and move "
"twice as fast. Engineers may also perform major terrain transformations (for "
"example, converting Tundra into Desert) which are beyond the capabilities of "
"Settlers. See the Terrain Alterations section for more details."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:428
msgid ""
"TIP 1: Upgrade Settlers to Engineers when possible, as Engineers require the "
"same resources as ordinary Settlers."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:431
msgid ""
"TIP 2: If you manage to build Leonardo's Workshop, research Explosives "
"before the Workshop becomes obsolete. This way, your Settler units will be "
"upgraded for free."
msgstr ""

