#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1059 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1060
msgid "?gui_type:Build Airstrip/Airbase"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1201 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1204
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1202
msgid ""
"Building an irrigation system on a suitable tile causes it to produce some "
"extra food each turn. Most tiles yield one extra food. A desert with a river "
"will yield two, if it is not already benefiting from an oasis."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1206 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1209
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1207
msgid ""
"Without knowledge of Electricity, irrigation requires a nearby source of "
"water: an ocean, lake, or river tile, or another tile with an irrigation "
"system, must share an edge (not just a corner) with the target tile. "
"However, once irrigated, land remains so even if the water source is "
"removed. Once Electricity is known, any suitable tile may be irrigated "
"without a water source."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1213
msgid ""
"Building irrigation on a tile with a mine or oil well will destroy the mine."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1215 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1189
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1165 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1163
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1219 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1216
msgid ""
"City center tiles get their terrain's irrigation bonus automatically, if "
"there is no conflicting mine or oil well on the tile. However, this does not "
"make cities count as a water source for further irrigation. Irrigation can "
"be built on the city tile simply to allow building further irrigation "
"elsewhere, but will not give the tile any further bonus."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1245 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1249
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1246
msgid ""
"Mines can be built on some types of terrain, which increases the number of "
"production points produced by that tile. Hills and Mountains get an extra 2 "
"production points per tile. Other terrains get 1 extra production point."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1255 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1227
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1203 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1201
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1259 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1256
msgid "Oil Well"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1276 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1280
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1277
msgid ""
"Once Refining is known, mines on Desert and Glacier tiles can be upgraded to "
"oil wells for an extra production point."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1282 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1286
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1283
#, fuzzy
msgid "Oil Platform"
msgstr "Petrolplatformo"

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1301 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1305
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1302
msgid ""
"Oil platforms allow cities with Offshore Platforms to get an extra "
"production point from Deep Ocean tiles."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1304 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1308
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1305
msgid ""
"Oil platforms can be built by Workers and similar units on board ships, or "
"directly by Transport units."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1327 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1331
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1328
msgid ""
"Pollution appears on tiles around cities with high production or population, "
"or when a Mfg. Plant suffers an industrial accident. It halves all output "
"from its tile, and contributes to the risk of global warming."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1332 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1336
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1333
msgid ""
"The pollution can only be cleared by dispatching Workers, Migrants, "
"Settlers, Engineers, or a Transport with the \"clean pollution\" order."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1342 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1346
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1343
msgid ""
"The city's population starts adding to pollution with the Factory, Super "
"Highways, Offshore Platform, and Mfg. Plant buildings. Each building causes "
"the population to add more to pollution. A Mass Transit will counteract the "
"pollution from two buildings in a city, and the Eiffel Tower wonder will "
"counteract the pollution from one building in all the owner's cities."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1353 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1295
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1271 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1270
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1357 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1354
msgid ""
"When an unused tile becomes polluted, there is the temptation to avoid the "
"effort of cleaning it, but the spread of pollution has far more terrible "
"results than the immediate economic impact -- every polluted tile increases "
"the chance of global warming. Each time global warming advances, the entire "
"world loses coastal land to the sea and to jungles and swamps, and inland "
"tiles are lost to desert. This tends to devastate cities and leads to global "
"impoverishment."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1386 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1328
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1304 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1303
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1390 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1387
msgid ""
"Villages (also called \"huts\") are primitive communities spread across the "
"world at the beginning of the game. Any land unit can enter a village, "
"making the village disappear and deliver a random response. If the village "
"proves hostile, it could produce barbarians or the unit entering may simply "
"be destroyed. If they are friendly, the player could receive gold, a new "
"technology, a military unit (occasionally a settler; and sometimes a unit "
"that the player cannot yet create), or even a new city."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1423 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1363
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1339 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1427
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once Refrigeration is known, irrigation systems can be upgraded to farmland "
"by irrigating them a second time. If the city working the tile has a "
"Supermarket, a farmland tile provides 50% more food. (Hence, farmland is "
"only useful on tiles which with irrigation yield 2 or more food.)"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1429 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1457
msgid "Farmland on a tile prevents any trade bonus from Super Highways."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1431 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1369
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1345 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1342
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1435 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1459
msgid "Like irrigation, farmland is incompatible with mines and oil wells."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1453 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1457
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1481
msgid ""
"Nuclear fallout can appear on tiles when a Nuclear unit is detonated, or "
"when a city's Nuclear Plant has an accident. It halves all output from its "
"tile."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1457 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1395
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1370 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1367
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1461 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1485
msgid ""
"Every tile with nuclear fallout also increases the risk of global nuclear "
"winter. If nuclear winter occurs, land across the globe changes into desert, "
"tundra, and ice, and lakes and oceans freeze."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1461 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1465
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1489
msgid ""
"Settlers, Workers, Migrants, Engineers, and Transport units can all clean up "
"nuclear fallout."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1467 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1495
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fort"
msgstr "Ekipu per defendilo"

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1493 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1520
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Forts are rapidly-built fortifications providing some defense (+50%) against "
"land units and boats. A fort is also necessary to start building a fortress."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1526 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1554
msgid ""
"Fortresses are more permanent forts. Construction on them can only begin "
"once the underlying fort is complete. Forts on River tiles cannot be "
"upgraded to Fortresses."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1530 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1558
msgid ""
"Compared to a fort, units in a fortress receive extra defense (+50%) against "
"all units (in total, their defense against land units and boats is doubled), "
"and do not count as aggressive if near a friendly city. Any kind of land "
"unit remaining in a fortress for a whole turn without moving recovers a "
"quarter of its hit points."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1536 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1540
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1564
msgid ""
"With Astronomy, fortresses gain watchtowers from which units can see further "
"afield."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1542 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1570
#, fuzzy
msgid "Airstrip"
msgstr "Aŭstria"

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1566
msgid ""
"Airstrips are rapidly-built runways allowing air units to land, refuel, and "
"recover outside cities. An aircraft remaining on an airstrip for a whole "
"turn without moving recovers a tenth of its hit points. This is, the same "
"amount it loses each turn while airborne. However, air units on an airstrip "
"are vulnerable to attack by land units."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1572 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1600
msgid ""
"Any units on an airstrip receive extra defense (+50%) against enemy aircraft."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1575 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1603
msgid "An airstrip is necessary to start building an airbase."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1605 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1634
msgid ""
"Airbases are more permanent airstrips. Construction on them can only begin "
"once the underlying airstrip is complete. Airstrips on River tiles cannot be "
"upgraded to Airbases."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1609
msgid ""
"Compared to an airstrip, units in an airbase receive extra defense (+50%) "
"against all units. In total, their defense against air units and missiles is "
"doubled, do not count as aggressive if near a friendly city, and can see "
"further afield. Also, air units recover more hit points -- a third per turn, "
"the same as in a city without an Airport."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1618 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1467
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1442 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1439
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1582 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1647
#, fuzzy
msgid "Buoy"
msgstr "Aĉetu"

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1640 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1488
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1463 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1460
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1604 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1670
msgid ""
"Buoys may be built in the ocean (by units on a sea-going vessel) to allow "
"their owner to see the surrounding tiles."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1646 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1494
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1469 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1466
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1610 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1679
#, fuzzy
msgid "Ruins"
msgstr "Plenumanta"

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1665 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1513
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1488 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1485
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1698
msgid ""
"Ruins mark the former site of a city that was destroyed or abandoned. They "
"have no effect on gameplay."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1694
msgid ""
"Roads allow your land units to move more quickly, and allow wheeled Big Land "
"units such as Chariots and Catapults to travel through otherwise difficult "
"terrain such as Mountains, Jungle, and Swamp."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1698 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1662
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1733
msgid "On some terrains, roads also provide a trade bonus."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1700 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1664
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1735
msgid ""
"Building roads on river tiles requires knowledge of Bridge Building. City "
"center tiles automatically get roads (even on a river tile)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1731 data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1552
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1695 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1766
msgid ""
"Once you learn the Railroad technology, you may upgrade your roads to "
"railroads. Units travel considerably faster along railroads than along roads."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1745 data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1566
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1709 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1780
msgid "Maglev"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1769 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1804
msgid ""
"With sufficient technology, you may build magnetic levitation systems along "
"your railroad routes. Land and Small Land units expend no movement points "
"when riding a maglev. You may ride indefinitely. (As may your enemies!)"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1774 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1738
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1809
msgid ""
"Your regular railroads are still used to carry heavy Big Land and Merchant "
"units for which the maglev system is unsuitable, and they continue to "
"provide production and trade bonuses."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1778 data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1597
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1742 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1813
msgid ""
"City center tiles with railroads are automatically upgraded to maglev when "
"you learn about Superconductors."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1800 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1764
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1834
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any land terrain type may have a River on it. A River adds 1 trade to the "
"resources produced by that tile. It also increases a tile's defense factor "
"by 25%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1804 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1768
msgid ""
"Land units may move along rivers for faster travel (but not diagonally). "
"Triremes may also travel up rivers (although later boats cannot)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1807
msgid ""
"Roads and railroads can only be built on River tiles if your civilization "
"has learned the Bridge Building technology. Fortresses and Airbases cannot "
"be built on River tiles."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1811 data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1775
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1847
msgid ""
"Cities built on or next to rivers incur a small risk of flooding, which will "
"destroy stored food."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1832 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1629
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1649 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1601
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1796
msgid ""
"Gold, when found on a Glacier, Hills, or Mountain tile, gives 6 more trade. "
"For more information, review the help for the individual tile types."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1891 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1688
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1708 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1660
msgid ""
"Furs, when found on a Tundra tile, gives 1 more food and 3 more trade. For "
"more information, review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:2158
msgid ""
"Spice(s), when found on a Swamp tile, gives 1 more food and 4 more trade. "
"For more information, review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:2219 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:2015
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:2035 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1987
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:2184
msgid ""
"Oil, when found on a Glacier or Desert tile, gives 3 more shields. For more "
"information, review the help for the individual tile types."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:33 data/royale/units.ruleset:34
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:33
msgid "Attack value halved when attacking Destroyer."
msgstr ""

