#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2871 data/royale/units.ruleset:2938
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2416
msgid "?spy_level:spymaster"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2358
msgid ""
"A Spy can also be used to:\n"
"\n"
" - sabotage an enemy unit reducing its hitpoints to half, if it is alone on "
"a tile and the players are at war;\n"
" - poison the water supply of an enemy city (reducing the population by "
"one);\n"
" - steal specific technology, with a reduced chance of success;\n"
" - steal further technologies from a city which has already been stolen "
"from. Cities become more resistant each time they are stolen from;\n"
" - sabotage predetermined city targets (with a reduced chance of success)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2374 data/royale/units.ruleset:2897
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2449
msgid ""
"Spies built under Communist or Federation governments will start at the "
"first veteran level (handler)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2406 data/royale/units.ruleset:3127
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2481
msgid ""
"A Caravan carries goods or material for trading with other nations, or to "
"help build wonders in your own cities."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2409 data/royale/units.ruleset:3130
msgid ""
"Caravans cannot take advantage of maglevs, but may travel on the railroads "
"that accompany them."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2412 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2488
msgid ""
"A Caravan sent to a foreign city (one not owned by an enemy) can establish a "
"trade route. The route's ongoing revenue is doubled if the two cities "
"involved are on different continents. Each city can support a maximum of two "
"trade routes."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2417 data/royale/units.ruleset:3135
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2493
msgid ""
"A Caravan sent to one of your own cities that is building a wonder can add "
"50 shields towards its production. If your city is not building a wonder, "
"the Caravan can take no special action."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2454 data/royale/units.ruleset:3172
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2530
msgid ""
"The Freight unit replaces the Caravan, and moves at twice the speed. It has "
"the same behavior and movement restrictions."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2489 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2565
msgid ""
"Explorers can also perform some actions in another player's city, and like "
"Diplomats and Spies, the unit is not consumed by these harmless actions:"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2506 data/classic/units.ruleset:2283
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2315 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2370
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3229 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2582
#, fuzzy
msgid "?unit:Leader"
msgstr "Estro"

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2540 data/classic/units.ruleset:2317
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2349 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2404
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3263 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2616
msgid "This is you. If you lose this unit, you lose the game. So do not."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2542 data/classic/units.ruleset:2319
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2351 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2406
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3265 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2618
msgid "Will not unleash barbarians from huts."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2589 data/classic/units.ruleset:2366
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2398 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2453
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3312 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2665
msgid "AWACS"
msgstr "AWACS"

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2615 data/classic/units.ruleset:2392
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2424 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2479
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3338 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2691
msgid ""
"The AWACS (Airborne Warning and Control System) is an airplane with an "
"advanced radar that can determine the location of enemy units over a wide "
"area."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:86
msgid ""
"Two cities with Airports can airlift one unit per turn.  Airlifting "
"instantly transports the unit from one city to another and will use all of "
"the unit's movement points. A unit must have some movement points left to be "
"airlifted."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:321
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Entertains the citizens of a city, making 3 unhappy citizens content. (Four "
"after the discovery of Electricity.) However, it does not affect citizens "
"made unhappy by military activity."
msgstr ""
"Ĝi amuzas la civitanoj de unu urbo kaj igas kontentaj tri malkontentaj "
"civitanoj (kaj kvar post la Elektroniko)."

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:347 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reduces the corruption in a city by 50%, and makes the revolt cost of the "
"city 4 times bigger. (These effects are redundant in your capital city.)"
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:351 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:358
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:352
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Under a Democracy, a Courthouse also makes 1 unhappy citizen content (unless "
"that citizen is unhappy about military activity)."
msgstr ""
"Ĝi malpliigas la konstruadon de urbo je 50%. Sub Demokratio, tribunalo igis "
"kontenta unu malkontentan civitanon. Krome ĝi duonigas la realan distancon "
"de la ĉefurbo por kalkuli la koston por inciti al ribelo."

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:449 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:478
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the effect of a Factory and Mfg. Plant on the shield production of "
"a city, and also reduces the amount of pollution generated by that "
"production. A Hydro Plant in combination with either a Factory or Mfg. Plant "
"gives a 75% production bonus over the level without any of these "
"improvements, while giving pollution only 75% of the equivalent combination "
"with a Power Plant. A Hydro Plant, Factory, and Mfg. Plant together give a "
"150% production bonus with pollution only 50% of the equivalent combination "
"with a Power Plant."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:485 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:540
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:480
#, no-c-format
msgid "Increases the science output in a city by 100%."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:507 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:634
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:592
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "Increases the luxury good and tax output in a city by 50%."
msgstr "Ĝi pliigas la sciencan produktadon je 50% en ĉiu urbo."

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:581 data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:573
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the effect of a Factory and Mfg. Plant on the shield production of "
"a city, and also reduces the amount of pollution generated by that "
"production. A Nuclear Plant in combination with either a Factory or Mfg. "
"Plant gives a 75% production bonus over the level without any of these "
"improvements, while giving pollution only 75% of the equivalent combination "
"with a Power Plant. A Nuclear Plant, Factory, and Mfg. Plant together give a "
"150% production bonus with pollution only 50% of the equivalent combination "
"with a Power Plant."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:651 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:708
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:636 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:785
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:741
msgid ""
"The cost to enemy Diplomats and Spies of inciting a revolt in a city also "
"depends upon the city's distance from the capital (under all forms of "
"government). Your capital city itself cannot be incited to revolt, and "
"enjoys a bonus when enemy agents try to evade your own agents stationed in "
"the city, or sabotage your buildings."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:666 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:723
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:651
#, c-format
msgid ""
"Under Despotism the city containing the palace gains a +75% production "
"bonus, and under Monarchy a +50% production bonus."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:741 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:800
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:723
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the effect of a Factory and Mfg. Plant on the shield production of "
"a city. A Power Plant in combination with either a Factory or Mfg. Plant "
"gives a 75% production bonus over the level without any of these "
"improvements. A Power Plant, Factory, and Mfg. Plant together give a 150% "
"production bonus. The extra production may lead to the city generating more "
"pollution."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:799 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:858
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:778
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Together with a Library, a Research Lab increases the science production of "
"a city by 200%. Together with a Library and a University, a Research Lab "
"increases the science production of a city by 450%."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:899 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:958
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:876
#, no-c-format
