#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3215
msgid ""
"GUIDE: The Explorer can be used to break the Zones of Control (ZoC) if an "
"enemy unit is blocking you. This can be very useful in situations where the "
"enemy is trying to limit your options by placing fortified units in "
"strategic locations next to rivers or roads. Simply move the Explorer to a "
"tile you want to go to and you can move unit(s) to a tile already occupied "
"by your own unit. The Explorer is also very good for checking who is next to "
"you and how far your enemies have already expanded. Many players consider "
"killing an Explorer as an act of war. This is why it sometimes makes sense "
"to warn before killing the explorer."
